should be camelcased so attribute tabindex-------->tabIndex
changes
--------

class------------->className
checked------------>defaultChecked (in radio button/checkbox) but checked also taking(but u need to specify onchange event else will throw error)
onchange----------->onChange
selected ---for option components
value-------------->defaultValue same like checked need to specify onchange for value attribute

styles
-------

const divStyle = {  //camelcased css styles are used and passed to style attribute rather than string
  color: 'blue',
  backgroundImage: 'url(' + imgUrl + ')',
};

const divStyle2 = {
  WebkitTransition: 'all', // note the capital 'W' here
  msTransition: 'all' // 'ms' is the only lowercase vendor prefix
};

function HelloWorldComponent() {
  return <div style={divStyle}>Hello World!</div>;
}

